UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Analysis by dev - 2026-01-08: ### Company Snapshot Problem & solution OpusCollect positions itself as an AI-first full-stack collections platform aimed at moving from pre-delinquency to hard-bucket collections, addressing a market with fragmented pan-India field operations and little scale in field-based collections. Market notes emphasize a gap in pan-India field collectors and a shift toward AI-enabled, data-driven recovery processes for banks and NBFCs. Ideal customer profile and pricing Direct clients include Unity Bank, Jana Bank, Avanti Finance, BikeBazaar, Branch, with additional through-partner channels (Fusion, ESAF, Cashe). Total assets under management ~₹900 crore; monthly collections ~₹6 crore. Pricing signals: - Take rates reported as 10% regular, 15% SMA, 20% for 90+ DP buckets. - Revenue drivers indicate 60–70% commission from collections, 15–18% automated legal services, 5–8% AI-driven collections, 2–8% data enrichment; for >90DPD, commissions can be 25–35% of amount collected. - For Kissht, a go-live target of ₹1 crore per month billing is noted. [Inference] Pricing appears to mix performance-based commissions with verticalized service fees; no formal external pricing sheet disclosed. Status of product & traction highlight Live, multi-channel field operations with AI/automation components: - In-house bot calling, route optimization, automated case allocation, and digital legal workflow. - Android field-collection app; real-time field tracking; 64k digital leg...' WHERE id = 323 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
